		<td><b>Okami Retro version</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Perhaps it's just me being slow to not find out about this until several months after, but I just dicovered that a Dragon Quest-like retro version of Okami is available at the <a href="http://www.cloverstudio.co.jp/o-kami/main.html" class="postlink">Okami official japanese site</a>.
<br />
<br />Incredibly cute, but the best part of this homage to the NES is that in the game, you can download NES-like MP3:s of the most memorable songs in the Okami soundtrack! There was one hidden song like this in the official soundtrack released, and I remember wanting to hear more at the time. Seems my wish just came true.
<br />
<br />And out of coincidence, I just bought this superb game earlier this day after noticing the PAL version has now been released over here. Now I just have to buy a PS2 cheap somewhere to be able to re-play it once again, non-pirated this time. Until then, this will make a neat substitute. :)
<br />
<br />For those of us who can't make out a single bit of the japanese, you can get all the retro tunes in an archive:
<br />
<br /><a href="http://www.gamingforce.com/forums/journal.php?action=view&amp;amount=single&amp;userid=69&amp;entryid=18369" class="postlink">http://www.gamingforce.com/forums/journal.php?action=view&amp;amount=single&amp;userid=69&amp;entryid=18369</a>
<br />
<br />I sure wish someone would rip and translate this retro game... =P

		

		</td>
	</tr>
